Different Ways to Format Strings in Java

Important:
- %s: String
- %c: Character
- %d: Integer (byte, short, int, long)
- %f: Float (float, double)

Width-Specifier:
- %10s - Left (String) Justification with a padding of 10.
- %-10s - Right (String) Justification with a padding of 10.
- %12d - Left (Integer) Justification with a padding of 12.
- %10.3f - Left (Double) Justification with a rounding to 3 decimal places.
- %.2f - Rounding to 2 decimal places.

